This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with active object recognition in cluttered scenes using attention mechanisms. The paper also mentions the use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) which is commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the proposed method can be applied to robotic vision tasks. The use of attention mechanisms and spatial transformer units also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions training the model using a 3D shape database, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of a differentiable 3D spatial transformer network for training with back-propagation suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
